00:00:53,321 --> 00:00:55,888
     narrator: spiral stairs    
     were part of a strategy    

10
00:00:55,890 --> 00:00:58,791
      to defend the towers      
      of medieval castles.      

11
00:00:58,793 --> 00:01:01,060
        attackers had to        
        climb single-file       

12
00:01:01,062 --> 00:01:04,196
       and couldn't storm       
     the castle all at once.    

13
00:01:04,198 --> 00:01:05,665
  and at the top of the stairs, 

14
00:01:05,667 --> 00:01:09,068
 the guardsmen could more easily
     maneuver their swords,     

15
00:01:09,070 --> 00:01:11,003
   giving them the upper hand.  

16
00:01:14,409 --> 00:01:16,942
    spiral stairs take people   
        to the next level       

17
00:01:16,944 --> 00:01:20,145
        without taking up       
         a lot of space.        

18
00:01:20,147 --> 00:01:23,482
    they're compact, and with   
   their corkscrew curvature,   

19
00:01:23,484 --> 00:01:27,620
        they can also be        
     architectural features.    

20
00:01:27,622 --> 00:01:29,956
     production starts with     
         the steel hubs         

21
00:01:29,958 --> 00:01:32,624
cut to the desired riser height.

22
00:01:32,626 --> 00:01:35,294
         a worker files         
     the sharp edges smooth     

23
00:01:35,296 --> 00:01:36,695
   and drills a threaded hole   

24
00:01:36,697 --> 00:01:39,966
  which will be used to fasten  
      the treads in place.      

25
00:01:42,370 --> 00:01:46,438
 a computer-driven plasma system
  cuts through a sheet of steel 

26
00:01:46,440 --> 00:01:51,309
    to produce the pie-shaped   
          stair treads.         

27
00:01:51,311 --> 00:01:53,712
    a worker nestles a tread    
           to the hub           

28
00:01:53,714 --> 00:01:56,248
         and clamps them        
       in a weld fixture.       

29
00:01:56,250 --> 00:01:58,384
         he also clamps         
       structural supports      

30
00:01:58,386 --> 00:02:02,187
    to the base of the tread.   

31
00:02:02,189 --> 00:02:04,590
       with everything in       
    the right configuration,    

32
00:02:04,592 --> 00:02:07,927
      he welds the supports     
    to the tread and the hub.   

33
00:02:07,929 --> 00:02:12,398
   he'll make 12 of these hub   
      and tread assemblies.     

34
00:02:12,400 --> 00:02:16,535
   he chips off the weld slag   
       for cleaner seams.       

35
00:02:16,537 --> 00:02:19,405
      a team slides the hub     
      and tread assemblies      

36
00:02:19,407 --> 00:02:20,940
      on to the center pole     

37
00:02:20,942 --> 00:02:24,076
        and rotates them        
    to the correct position.    

38
00:02:24,078 --> 00:02:27,346
       the design geometry      
     dictates the rotation.     

39
00:02:27,348 --> 00:02:29,148
     once rotated correctly,    

40
00:02:29,150 --> 00:02:31,650
   the workers fasten the hubs  
           to the pole          

41
00:02:31,652 --> 00:02:34,053
       and add a platform       
        for the top step.       

42
00:02:36,757 --> 00:02:40,826
  a baluster spins in a lathe,  
    as tools cut it to length   

43
00:02:40,828 --> 00:02:44,096
        and round the end       
    to the correct diameter.    

44
00:02:44,098 --> 00:02:46,565
      the operator measures     
          the diameter.         

45
00:02:46,567 --> 00:02:48,768
   he inserts the rounded end   
            in a dye            

46
00:02:48,770 --> 00:02:52,905
 that carves the thread into it.

47
00:02:52,907 --> 00:02:54,773
   a worker welds a steel cup   

48
00:02:54,775 --> 00:02:57,777
  just above the threaded part  
        of the baluster.        

49
00:02:57,779 --> 00:02:59,712
      this cup will support     
          the baluster          

50
00:02:59,714 --> 00:03:02,114
    once it's been installed    
         on the thread.         

51
00:03:02,116 --> 00:03:04,850
    he grinds the weld scale    
          from the cup.         

52
00:03:04,852 --> 00:03:07,052
     he inserts the baluster    
          through holes         

53
00:03:07,054 --> 00:03:09,121
 in a metal spacer in the tread.

54
00:03:09,123 --> 00:03:12,258
  he screws a nut on to the end 
          to secure it.         

55
00:03:14,662 --> 00:03:18,464
   using rollers now, another   
    worker twists long strips   

56
00:03:18,466 --> 00:03:21,333
     of metal into spiraling    
      hand rails that match     

57
00:03:21,335 --> 00:03:23,736
     the rise of the stairs.    

58
00:03:23,738 --> 00:03:26,004
        he fits the rail        
      to the top balusters      

59
00:03:26,006 --> 00:03:29,542
     and clamps it in place.    

60
00:03:29,544 --> 00:03:33,078
   he then welds the balusters  
          to the rail.          

61
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:36,214
   he adds more railing until   
   it spirals all the way down  

62
00:03:36,216 --> 00:03:39,284
       to the first step.       

63
00:03:39,286 --> 00:03:42,688
       the team secures it      
        to the platform.        

64
00:03:42,690 --> 00:03:46,492
  the spiral staircase's metal  
   structure is now complete.   

65
00:03:46,494 --> 00:03:48,828
         it's ready for         
       the wooden accents.      

66
00:03:50,965 --> 00:03:54,499
      a worker applies glue     
      to pieces of red oak.     

67
00:03:54,501 --> 00:03:57,636
      he'll use two of them     
    to make one stair tread.    

68
00:03:57,638 --> 00:04:01,574
   he clamps two tread sets in  
 a fixture while the glue sets. 

69
00:04:01,576 --> 00:04:03,108
        he inserts a shim       

70
00:04:03,110 --> 00:04:07,312
     and tightens the clamp     
   to apply downward pressure.  

71
00:04:07,314 --> 00:04:10,850
    once the glue has cured,    
    a planer shaves the tread   

72
00:04:10,852 --> 00:04:14,920
         perfectly flat         
  and to the desired thickness. 

73
00:04:14,922 --> 00:04:16,789
   after refining the profile,  

74
00:04:16,791 --> 00:04:21,127
   a worker rounds the edge of  
 the stair tread using a router.

75
00:04:22,863 --> 00:04:25,264
   after gluing strips of wood  
       together to create       

76
00:04:25,266 --> 00:04:28,868
        a curved railing,       
  he sands the excess adhesive, 

77
00:04:28,870 --> 00:04:32,338
        and with a file,        
    removes more of the glue.   

78
00:04:32,340 --> 00:04:36,408
    he turns the railing over   
and carves a groove in the wood.

79
00:04:36,410 --> 00:04:38,677
  this will enable the railing  
         to be installed        

80
00:04:38,679 --> 00:04:40,879
  over the metal rail support.  

81
00:04:40,881 --> 00:04:44,750
     he adds some detailing     
         along the edge.        

82
00:04:44,752 --> 00:04:46,685
        a team then fits        
       the wooden railing       

83
00:04:46,687 --> 00:04:49,154
 to the metal support structure.

84
00:04:49,156 --> 00:04:53,225
    all of the rail sections    
     fit together perfectly.    

85
00:04:53,227 --> 00:04:56,027
       after the pre-fit,       
     they remove the railing    

86
00:04:56,029 --> 00:04:58,430
      and sculpt the edges      
         to be rounder.         

87
00:04:58,432 --> 00:05:03,368
  the rounded edges complement  
   the overall spiral design.   

88
00:05:03,370 --> 00:05:06,972
  a worker pre-fits the wooden  
  treads to the metal structure 

89
00:05:06,974 --> 00:05:10,509
      and then disassembles     
   the entire spiral staircase  

90
00:05:10,511 --> 00:05:12,211
   for painting and staining.   

91
00:05:14,382 --> 00:05:17,983
the spiral stairs are then ready
 for reassembly in the building 

92
00:05:17,985 --> 00:05:19,651
     they were designed for.    

93
00:05:19,653 --> 00:05:24,323
they'll definitely add a certain
  twist to the interior design. 

94
